    // Statement: Correlation (Diverse -> High Innovation).
    // A. "Directly causes" (Too strong, correlation != causation).
    // B. "Should prioritize" (Prescriptive/Recommendation, good conclusion).
    // C. "More likely to generate" (Restating the finding mostly).
    // D. "Impossible" (Too extreme).
    // Usually, conclusions from such studies in aptitude tests favor B (Actionable advice) or C (Probabilistic inference).
