    options: ["d e b a c", "b d e a c", "d e a b c", "d b e a c"],
    // Logical Order: 
    // d. A report is organized in sections. (Topic Sentence)
    // b. Each section should have an underlined heading. (Detail about sections)
    // a. The report should include the following (Transition)
    // c. The intro... (List of what it includes)
    // e. It is about cultivating... (This sentence seems unrelated to report structure? Wait, let's check context. Ah, question 2 starts with 'It is about...'. The first block has 5 sentences? No, text says a,b,c,d. Then Q2 starts. Let's re-read carefully.)
