    // Logical flow: Belief -> Definition -> Rich/Poor -> Money -> Skin Color.
    // b -> a -> d -> e -> c. 
    // Wait, option B is b a e d c. Option C is b d e c a.
    // Let's try D: d a e c a (Ends with a?).
    // Let's try A: d e c a b.
    // Most logical is starting with 'I believe' (b).
    // Let's assume C (b d e c a).
    // b (Education) -> d (Same for anyone) -> e (Money doesn't matter) -> c (Color doesn't matter) -> a (Cultivating mind).
    // 'a' feels like a definition that should be early.
    // However, 'c' "It ALSO doesn't matter" follows 'e'. So e -> c link is strong.
